
Problem 4: Precision Checker
Goal: See the difference between float and double precision.
Input: Read a precise number (like 3.1415926535) into both a float and a double variable.
Output: Print both variables using the format specifier %.10f to see where the float loses accuracy.



CODE:

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    float f;
    double d;

    // Read the same precise number into both variables
    printf("Enter a precise number (e.g., 3.1415926535): ");
    scanf("%lf", &d); // Read into double first

    f = (float)d; // Assign double value to float

    // Print both with 10 decimal places
    printf("Float  : %.10f\n", f);
    printf("Double : %.10f\n", d);

    return 0;
}

OUTPUT:

Enter a precise number (e.g., 3.1415926535): 4.5433345566677654
